# Roadmap

This directory is the **source of truth** for all roadmap-tracked work.
It contains multiple **tracks** in a single unified backlog. It is
structured to be read by both humans and the scheduled automation
agents (see [`AUTOMATION.md`](./AUTOMATION.md)).

> **Ad-hoc issues** (collaborator bug reports not on any roadmap) are
> handled separately by the ad-hoc agent -- see
> [`docs/roadmap-adhoc/`](../roadmap-adhoc/).

## Layout

```
docs/roadmap/
+-- README.md               <-- you are here
+-- AUTOMATION.md           <-- how the scheduled agents work
+-- BACKLOG.yml             <-- unified, multi-track work queue (version 2)
+-- AGENT_PROMPT.md         <-- runtime contract for all roadmap agents
+-- epics/                  <-- epic-level specs
+-- items/                  <-- per-item specs (one file per BACKLOG.yml entry)
```

## How to use this

### Reading order (new contributor / fresh agent)

1. This file (scope + conventions).
2. `AUTOMATION.md` (how items move, when, under whose authority).
3. `BACKLOG.yml` (what's next -- pick your track).
4. The relevant `epics/*.md` for context on *why*.
5. The specific `items/<id>-*.md` for *what to build*.

### Conventions

- **Epics** are stable containers for a theme. They rarely change.
- **Items** are concrete, shippable units -- each item is one merge.
  Items are the thing the agent picks up.
- **Status** lives in `BACKLOG.yml`, never in per-item files.
- **Dependencies** are explicit and within the same track. The agent
  will only pick up an item whose deps are all `done` or `staged`.
- **No cross-track deps.** If items across tracks depend on each
  other, restructure.
- **Acceptance criteria** are checklists inside each item file. An
  item is `done` only when every box is checked AND the branch is
  merged to `${__PROD_BRANCH}`.

### Status values (in `BACKLOG.yml`)

| Status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `ready` | In the backlog. Agent picks it up when deps are satisfied. |
| `in-progress` | Feature branch merged to staging, CI running. |
| `staged` | CI green on staging. Main PR opened. Awaiting human review + merge. |
| `done` | PR merged to `${__PROD_BRANCH}`, production deploy verified, issue closed. |
| `blocked` | Unmet deps OR a failure the agent couldn't fix. Agent skips. |
| `deferred` | Explicitly shelved. Agent skips. |

State transitions the agent performs: `ready -> in-progress -> staged`.
The `staged -> done` transition happens when a **human** merges the
PR into `${__PROD_BRANCH}`, triggering the auto-deploy pipeline.

## Relationship to `${__PROD_BRANCH}` and prod

The agent **does not touch `${__PROD_BRANCH}`** except for BACKLOG.yml
status updates. Its merge target is `${__STAGING_BRANCH}`. A feature
branch only lands on `${__PROD_BRANCH}` when you merge it yourself.
